==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Photographone
<hw>Pho*tog"ra*phone</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Photograph</er>; <er>-phone</er>.]</ety> <def>A device, consisting
essentially of an electric arc and a camera, by which a series of
photographs of the variations of the arc due to sound waves are obtained
for reproduction by means of a selenium cell and a telephone.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

